= Twisted Community = 

For interacting with the twisted community members, you have several options:

== Mail Lists ==

Mail list subscription information as well as list archives are available for the following lists:
 * [http://twistedmatrix.com/cgi-bin/mailman/listinfo/twisted-python twisted-python]
 * [http://twistedmatrix.com/cgi-bin/mailman/listinfo/twisted-web twisted-web]
 * [https://mailman.ik.nu/mailman/listinfo/twisted-jabber twisted-jabber]

You can subscribe to these mailing lists above.

== Stack Overflow ==

Stack Overflow is a programming Q & A site.  You can find Twisted-related questions there, often with answers:

  * http://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/twisted

== Real-Time Chat ==

Server: {{{irc.freenode.net}}} (more about [http://freenode.net the Freenode IRC network])

For support, you can join one of several channels:

  - [irc://irc.freenode.net/twisted #twisted] | [https://botbot.me/freenode/twisted/ Logs] - support for all Twisted packages except Twisted Web
  - [irc://irc.freenode.net/twisted.web #twisted.web] | [https://botbot.me/freenode/twisted-dev/ Logs] - support for Twisted Web; both for development with it and deploying it
  - [irc://irc.freenode.net/divmod #divmod] - support for and development of [https://launchpad.net/divmod.org technologies related to Twisted] such as the Nevow templating system.

If you're working on Twisted, you should join the development channel.

  - [irc://irc.freenode.net/twisted-dev #twisted-dev] | [https://botbot.me/freenode/twisted-dev/ Logs] - for development of Twisted

